@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Korners' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any space, whether it is occupied or not. If
the space is already occupied, the Korner that is shown on that
space will be replaced by the next Korner (the Korner that is
displayed under the 'Next' text at the right of the game board)
and the Korner that was on the clicked space will become the next
Korner. If the space was empty, the next Korner will go there...

  An indicator showing the minimum number of Korners of the same
type to include in a square appears at the right of the game board,
under the 'Same type Korners in square' text. As the game
progresses, that number will increase until it gets to 4. If you
create a square with less than that number of same type Korners,
the square will remain there...

  As a square is formed, the number of points you get will be
according to the highest number of Korners of the same type that
is included in the square: 2 Korners will give 1 point, 3 Korners
will give 10 points and 4 Korners will give 100 points.

  Avoid completely filling the 8 by 8 spaces gamboard, when that
happens, the game ends...

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

